1
00:00:09,679 --> 00:00:10,880
So in the end,

2
00:00:11,880 --> 00:00:13,160
you still don't believe me.

3
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:16,559
Turn around.

4
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:17,679
Don't move!

5
00:00:17,679 --> 00:00:18,640
Turn around!

6
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:20,039
Boss.

7
00:00:20,359 --> 00:00:21,239
Nobody move!

8
00:00:21,239 --> 00:00:21,920
Li Kaiyang.

9
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:24,359
A real man

10
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:26,160
owns up to what he's done.

11
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:28,640
Don't add to your crimes out of recklessness.

12
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:09,680
Why would I kidnap her?

13
00:01:10,959 --> 00:01:12,359
Ruolan is the woman I love.

14
00:01:13,079 --> 00:01:13,680
I...

15
00:01:13,879 --> 00:01:15,280
I was taking her out for some air.

16
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:16,799
And you call that kidnapping?

17
00:01:17,319 --> 00:01:18,840
You stuffed her in a suitcase.

18
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:20,840
You call that getting some air?

19
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:23,400
Do you have X-ray vision?

20
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:26,280
How did you know there was a person inside?

21
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,640
If this is how you cops work cases,

22
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:30,120
you'll be a laughingstock.

23
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:33,120
Then how do you explain the red gloves?

24
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,120
It's just a personal preference.

25
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:37,159
Is that against the law?

26
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:38,439
Huh?

27
00:01:38,959 --> 00:01:40,400
What color gloves I choose to wear,

28
00:01:40,799 --> 00:01:41,959
is that the cops' business too?

29
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:43,599
These red gloves

30
00:01:43,599 --> 00:01:45,920
are identical to the ones Ma Shijiang used.

31
00:01:46,239 --> 00:01:47,719
And you and Ma Shijiang were classmates.

32
00:01:47,719 --> 00:01:48,920
You've also committed crimes together.

33
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:49,879
Isn't that the truth?

34
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:50,719
Yes.

35
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,519
But what does that prove?

36
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:54,920
That I'm guilty?

37
00:01:55,879 --> 00:01:57,280
Since I graduated from high school,

38
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:58,920
I haven't seen Ma Shijiang again.

39
00:01:59,799 --> 00:02:00,640
Xing Mingliang,

40
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:04,159
I'm only being polite for Chief Xing's sake.

41
00:02:05,079 --> 00:02:06,560
Don't make me do this the hard way.

42
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:10,840
I'm sorry,

43
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,159
Uncle Wang.

44
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,840
I shouldn't have made you angry.

45
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:16,759
Actually,

46
00:02:17,639 --> 00:02:18,800
the reason I came today

47
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,960
was to seek help for Ruolan.

48
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,599
What exactly are you trying to say?

49
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,080
Just spit it out.

50
00:02:31,639 --> 00:02:34,039
The reason I took Ruolan away

51
00:02:36,639 --> 00:02:37,400
was...

52
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:42,159
to hide from a very terrifying person.

53
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,599
Someone more terrifying than you?

54
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:48,879
Haven't you noticed?

55
00:02:50,479 --> 00:02:51,680
Right beside you,

56
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,599
hidden all along,

57
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,719
is an extremely terrifying person.

58
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:57,039
I told you,

59
00:02:57,439 --> 00:02:58,680
just spit it out.

60
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,439
What are you trying to say?

61
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,400
The reason I took Ruolan away

62
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:03,759
is...

63
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:05,599
is, is because

64
00:03:06,479 --> 00:03:09,280
we know who killed bank president Su Zhuang.

65
00:03:11,719 --> 00:03:13,039
The knife used to kill him

66
00:03:13,199 --> 00:03:13,800
was...

67
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,919
was the fruit knife from my home.

68
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:18,719
Have you even seen the evidence?

69
00:03:18,719 --> 00:03:20,199
And you claim the knife is yours?

70
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,639
Because of someone,

71
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:27,719
a very terrifying person.

72
00:03:29,199 --> 00:03:29,800
I'm leaving.

73
00:03:30,199 --> 00:03:31,400
Hey, Brother Li.

74
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,319
I'll show Ruolan around the room.

75
00:03:34,479 --> 00:03:36,039
Could you cut an apple for us?

76
00:03:36,639 --> 00:03:37,159
Sure.

77
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,319
There's a new fruit knife in the kitchen.

78
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:41,159
Come on, Ruolan.

79
00:03:41,439 --> 00:03:41,960
Let's go.

80
00:04:11,759 --> 00:04:12,319
Ruolan,

81
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,199
It's time we turned a new page.

82
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:21,720
I wish you...

83
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:22,759
I wish you both...

84
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,480
a happy life together from now on.

85
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:28,240
Thank you, Brother Li.

86
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:29,319
I have something to attend to.

87
00:04:29,319 --> 00:04:30,000
I'll be going now.

88
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:32,040
I won't see you out.

89
00:04:40,959 --> 00:04:43,199
What exactly are you trying to say?

90
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,000
Uncle Wang.

91
00:04:44,399 --> 00:04:46,120
I... I've already said so much.

92
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,160
Isn't it clear to you yet?

93
00:04:47,959 --> 00:04:48,759
Li Kaiyang.

94
00:04:49,079 --> 00:04:50,680
Why did he take Su Zhuang out of the ward?

95
00:04:51,439 --> 00:04:53,319
And why did Su Zhuang end up dead in the woods?

96
00:04:54,079 --> 00:04:55,199
How do you know all this?

97
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,920
Someone called and told me.

98
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,040
There was no caller ID.

99
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:01,839
And the voice was unfamiliar.

100
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,879
On the phone, he told me

101
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:05,360
that he was

102
00:05:09,519 --> 00:05:11,199
a friend of Captain Zhao, Zhao Qingming.

103
00:05:12,759 --> 00:05:13,439
He said he

104
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,720
didn't want to see Ruolan get hurt again either.

105
00:05:16,959 --> 00:05:17,680
He...

106
00:05:18,199 --> 00:05:19,519
He also told me

107
00:05:19,519 --> 00:05:22,519
that Su Zhuang's death was linked to Li Kaiyang.

108
00:05:23,399 --> 00:05:24,879
If you don't believe me, check the call records.

109
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:27,120
We will certainly check the call records.

110
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,519
But based on that alone,

111
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,720
how can you say Captain Li was involved in Su Zhuang's death?

112
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,199
It was only later,

113
00:05:36,519 --> 00:05:37,360
when I was tidying the kitchen,

114
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,279
that I noticed

115
00:05:38,839 --> 00:05:40,160
a fruit knife was missing.

116
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:41,879
Is this the knife?

117
00:05:43,199 --> 00:05:43,800
That's right.

118
00:05:44,079 --> 00:05:44,639
This...

119
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,360
This is the fruit knife from my home.

120
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:49,240
If you don't believe me, you can verify it.

121
00:05:49,759 --> 00:05:50,680
Take a look at this knife.

122
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,399
See if it matches the knife block at my home.

123
00:05:53,279 --> 00:05:54,000
Xing Mingliang.

124
00:05:54,319 --> 00:05:55,680
Framing a public official

125
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:56,680
carries legal consequences.

126
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:57,439
Do you understand?

127
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:58,519
Xing Mingliang.

128
00:05:59,879 --> 00:06:01,879
A homicide case is a grave matter.

129
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:04,199
Do you know the consequences of lying?

130
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,680
I haven't told a single lie.

131
00:06:10,439 --> 00:06:12,279
I'm willing to take full responsibility,

132
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,279
as long as you

133
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:16,160
can keep me and Ruolan safe.

134
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,519
What right do you have to frame my Boss?

135
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,319
Huh?

136
00:06:20,319 --> 00:06:21,480
What nonsense are you spouting?

137
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,519
How dare you frame Captain Li!

138
00:06:22,639 --> 00:06:23,319
Jiang Han!

139
00:06:23,319 --> 00:06:24,199
I'm asking you!

140
00:06:24,639 --> 00:06:25,399
Someone, come!

141
00:06:26,279 --> 00:06:26,959
Jiang Han.

142
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,120
Take him out to cool off.

143
00:06:33,879 --> 00:06:35,240
Everything you've said,

144
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:38,199
I will verify word by word.

145
00:06:39,959 --> 00:06:40,560
All right.

146
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:07,439
Get down.

147
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:09,800
Dad.

148
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,480
What are you doing?

149
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,879
You are no son of mine.

150
00:07:14,959 --> 00:07:15,480
Dad.

151
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,800
You're a cop. You can't do this.

152
00:07:18,279 --> 00:07:19,120
A cop?

153
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,639
So you do know I'm a cop.

154
00:07:21,319 --> 00:07:22,199
You knew I'm a cop,

155
00:07:22,199 --> 00:07:23,879
yet you still did such heinous things?

156
00:07:24,199 --> 00:07:25,839
How did I raise you?

157
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,079
Raise me?

158
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,920
When did you ever truly raise me?

159
00:07:31,079 --> 00:07:32,519
The reason I've become what I am today

160
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:34,519
is all because of you.

161
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,279
Go on, hit me. Come on.

162
00:07:39,279 --> 00:07:39,959
Keep hitting me.

163
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:40,680
Beat me to death.

164
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:41,800
Hit me!

165
00:07:42,639 --> 00:07:43,879
Ever since Mom died,

166
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,000
every day for me has been worse than death.

167
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,319
Don't bring up your mother in front of me.

168
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:49,399
If you hadn't been so willful as a child,

169
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:50,199
It's all because of you

170
00:07:50,199 --> 00:07:51,199
that my mom died.

171
00:07:51,399 --> 00:07:52,040
Yes.

172
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,920
I failed to take care of you both.

173
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:56,399
But...

174
00:07:57,399 --> 00:07:59,079
But my job didn't allow it.

175
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,519
Just three days after Mom died,

176
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:05,240
you dumped me with Grandma.

177
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,040
In your heart,

178
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:08,160
I'll never matter as much as your damn cases.

179
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,319
You...

180
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:13,639
You're the main culprit who caused Mom's death.

181
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,600
You have no right to lecture me.

182
00:08:18,079 --> 00:08:19,319
I raised you from a young age,

183
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,160
and you say I have no right to lecture you?

184
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,439
You don't have the right.

185
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,480
When I was five,

186
00:08:29,439 --> 00:08:30,680
other kids,

187
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:33,320
when sick, had their moms to care for them.

188
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:34,960
But me?

189
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:36,960
I only had Grandma.

190
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,080
Every day when I woke up,

191
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:41,600
I would ask,

192
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,159
"Where's Daddy?"

193
00:08:44,879 --> 00:08:46,000
"Where's my daddy?"

194
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:47,639
Back then,

195
00:08:48,159 --> 00:08:49,320
where were you?

196
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,519
Answer me.

197
00:08:54,759 --> 00:08:55,639
Where were you?

198
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,799
Busy with your damn cases, weren't you?

199
00:09:02,039 --> 00:09:03,399
When I was in middle school,

200
00:09:04,159 --> 00:09:05,360
I was being bullied.

201
00:09:06,399 --> 00:09:07,960
They took my things,

202
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:11,240
holding knives at me like this.

203
00:09:11,399 --> 00:09:13,080
I was scared going to school every day,

204
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,559
constantly on edge.

205
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,480
And I told you about it.

206
00:09:17,519 --> 00:09:18,679
What did you say to me?

207
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:19,840
You said,

208
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:22,440
"You're the son of a detective captain."

209
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,120
"Don't cause trouble."

210
00:09:24,279 --> 00:09:25,559
"Just study hard."

211
00:09:25,919 --> 00:09:27,919
How I longed for you to be like a hero

212
00:09:27,919 --> 00:09:29,000
and protect me.

213
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:29,679
Dad.

214
00:09:30,039 --> 00:09:30,679
Mingliang.

215
00:09:32,919 --> 00:09:33,919
This is all my fault.

216
00:09:35,919 --> 00:09:37,120
I'm sorry I failed you.

217
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,799
What's the point of saying this now?

218
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:43,559
It just proves that you...

219
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,559
You're a hypocrite.

220
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:49,360
You're so fake.

221
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,720
Everything I did afterwards,

222
00:09:53,279 --> 00:09:54,200
skipping class,

223
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:55,679
fighting,

224
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,559
talking back to teachers,

225
00:09:59,399 --> 00:10:01,399
I just wanted you to care a little more.

226
00:10:01,679 --> 00:10:02,360
And you?

227
00:10:02,639 --> 00:10:05,240
You never once asked me what I wanted.

228
00:10:05,799 --> 00:10:07,080
Now let me tell you.

229
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:17,480
Daddy.

230
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,399
Daddy.

231
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,600
I just wanted a dad.

232
00:10:24,159 --> 00:10:24,960
A dad who could,

233
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:27,799
when I was sad,

234
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,480
when I was hurt,

235
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:30,480
when I was afraid,

236
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,759
protect me.

237
00:10:33,039 --> 00:10:35,679
I just wanted a dad.

238
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:41,200
Stop putting on this heartbroken act.

239
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:42,879
Aren't you going to throw me in prison?

240
00:10:42,879 --> 00:10:44,240
Come on, do it!

241
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:46,159
Do it!

242
00:10:56,559 --> 00:10:57,240
Go.

243
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,320
The farther away, the better.

244
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:04,440
Cut all ties with Xu Wenwen.

245
00:11:06,159 --> 00:11:08,240
Just live an honest life as a good man.

246
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,639
You think this will make me forgive you?

247
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,240
Let me tell you,

248
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:20,360
in your dreams.

249
00:11:25,759 --> 00:11:26,480
I hate you.

250
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:30,639
I hate you to death.

251
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,399
I'll never forgive you as long as I live.

252
00:12:11,039 --> 00:12:11,840
It's over.

253
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:13,480
Chief Xing.

254
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:15,600
You really don't look well.

255
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:16,799
Maybe you should...

256
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:18,799
Just do your job.

257
00:12:20,759 --> 00:12:21,759
Mingliang has confessed.

258
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,360
He said it was Li Kaiyang

259
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,039
who took the knife from his place

260
00:12:25,519 --> 00:12:27,399
and used it to kill Su Zhuang.

261
00:12:28,399 --> 00:12:29,639
That's complete nonsense.

262
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:32,080
But there's no proof yet that he's lying.

263
00:12:32,519 --> 00:12:33,120
And what's more,

264
00:12:33,399 --> 00:12:35,480
he's provided evidence to back it up.

265
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:37,039
Let's go.

266
00:12:37,159 --> 00:12:38,120
Time to interrogate Li Kaiyang.

267
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:51,480
All of you, get out.

268
00:12:55,679 --> 00:12:56,320
Chief Xing.

269
00:12:56,639 --> 00:12:57,639
He's not in cuffs.

270
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,000
It's fine.

271
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,200
Xing Mingliang said

272
00:13:15,679 --> 00:13:17,120
the knife used to kill Su Zhuang

273
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,679
was the one you took from his home.

274
00:13:20,639 --> 00:13:22,000
That's a vicious move.

275
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,360
Do you really believe this childish trick?

276
00:13:26,039 --> 00:13:27,759
Do you have evidence to refute him?

277
00:13:30,759 --> 00:13:32,080
At Xing Mingliang's home, I did

278
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,720
use an identical fruit knife

279
00:13:34,399 --> 00:13:35,200
to cut an apple.

280
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,440
Then you took that knife,

281
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,240
and used it to kill Su Zhuang.

282
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,799
Because the others arrived too quickly,

283
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:43,159
you had no time to flee,

284
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:45,080
so you tossed the knife aside,

285
00:13:45,759 --> 00:13:47,559
then pretended to save Su Zhuang,

286
00:13:48,279 --> 00:13:49,480
putting on a show for everyone.

287
00:13:49,919 --> 00:13:50,480
Right?

288
00:13:51,039 --> 00:13:52,279
This story is full of holes.

289
00:13:52,279 --> 00:13:53,480
There's no way you can't see them.

290
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:56,480
Of course,

291
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:59,440
if this is the result you want,

292
00:14:01,039 --> 00:14:02,279
then that's a different story.

293
00:14:02,399 --> 00:14:03,279
What do you mean?

294
00:14:06,039 --> 00:14:06,919
You suspect me?

295
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:08,360
Li Kaiyang,

296
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:09,919
if you want to prove

297
00:14:10,399 --> 00:14:12,200
you weren't involved in Su Zhuang's death,

298
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,720
give me a reasonable explanation

299
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,320
and solid evidence.

300
00:14:19,159 --> 00:14:21,200
If you use Qin Hui's trumped-up charges,

301
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,759
no explanation from me will matter.

302
00:14:27,279 --> 00:14:28,559
So in the end,

303
00:14:29,559 --> 00:14:30,879
you still don't believe me.

304
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:34,159
Turn around.

305
00:14:34,879 --> 00:14:35,440
Don't move!

306
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,360
Turn around!

307
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:37,799
Boss.

308
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:39,000
Nobody move!

309
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:39,720
Li Kaiyang.

310
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,039
A real man

311
00:14:42,759 --> 00:14:43,960
owns up to what he's done.

312
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:46,399
Don't add to your crimes out of recklessness.

313
00:14:46,679 --> 00:14:47,320
Li Kaiyang,

314
00:14:47,759 --> 00:14:49,879
you're forcing yourself into a dead end.

315
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:51,440
Listen to Chief Xing.

316
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,960
It's not too late to lower the gun.

317
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:55,399
I have no choice.

318
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:57,799
Give me some time.

319
00:14:59,039 --> 00:14:59,679
Seven days.

320
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,519
I'll get to the bottom of this.

321
00:15:03,279 --> 00:15:04,360
I'll give everyone an answer.

322
00:15:04,559 --> 00:15:05,240
Boss,

323
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:07,240
we all know you're being framed,

324
00:15:07,559 --> 00:15:08,639
but what you're doing now

325
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:10,120
is cutting off your own way out!

326
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,360
Listen to Uncle Xing and Captain Wang.

327
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:13,639
Put the gun down first.

328
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,240
I'll say this one last time.

329
00:15:16,399 --> 00:15:17,559
Everyone, step back!

330
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:19,360
Step back!

331
00:15:20,679 --> 00:15:21,519
Step back!

332
00:15:39,399 --> 00:15:41,320
Li Kaiyang, think this through!

333
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:42,840
Don't do anything rash!

334
00:15:43,279 --> 00:15:44,120
Stay back!

335
00:15:45,759 --> 00:15:46,480
Boss.

336
00:15:48,759 --> 00:15:49,440
Calm down.

337
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:51,240
Captain Li.

338
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:52,679
Stay back!

339
00:15:53,159 --> 00:15:53,759
Boss.

340
00:15:53,759 --> 00:15:55,000
Everyone, stay back!

341
00:15:55,559 --> 00:15:56,600
Tell them to stay back!

342
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:57,399
Stay back!

343
00:15:58,440 --> 00:15:59,360
Get back up onto the steps!

344
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:02,799
Hurry up!

345
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:07,360
The car keys.

346
00:16:27,039 --> 00:16:28,000
Close the door for me.

347
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:38,919
Forget it.

348
00:16:41,519 --> 00:16:42,759
Given his driving skills and experience,

349
00:16:42,879 --> 00:16:43,759
and it being nighttime,

350
00:16:43,759 --> 00:16:44,600
there's no way you'll catch him.

351
00:16:45,279 --> 00:16:46,039
But your gun...

352
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:47,480
It's over there.

353
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:48,879
He just tossed it out the window.

354
00:16:51,799 --> 00:16:53,000
Issue a wanted notice immediately.

355
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:54,679
Citywide manhunt for Li Kaiyang.

356
00:16:54,879 --> 00:16:55,600
Yes, sir.

357
00:17:04,079 --> 00:17:04,680
Boss.

358
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:07,359
Something's happened.

359
00:17:12,119 --> 00:17:14,079
Xing Junfeng really is useless.

360
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:16,960
Can't even contain a mere deputy captain.

361
00:17:17,759 --> 00:17:19,880
Boss, Li Kaiyang is a terrifying man.

362
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,839
What should we do next?

363
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:22,799
What's there to panic about?

364
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,079
The sky isn't falling yet.

365
00:17:25,519 --> 00:17:26,119
Boss.

366
00:17:26,759 --> 00:17:28,039
Li Kaiyang is meticulous,

367
00:17:28,039 --> 00:17:28,839
brave and resourceful.

368
00:17:29,839 --> 00:17:31,279
He never quits until he gets results.

369
00:17:31,359 --> 00:17:33,160
I'm afraid he'll uncover the truth.

370
00:17:33,839 --> 00:17:34,640
That's exactly why...

371
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:36,640
I can't let him

372
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:39,240
ruin everything I've built over the years.

373
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,599
So what should we do?

374
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:42,559
Just give the order.

375
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:46,039
He's already had his chance.

376
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:47,400
So,

377
00:17:48,359 --> 00:17:50,079
let's cut this knot with a sharp blade.

378
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:51,000
Understood.

379
00:17:52,039 --> 00:17:53,319
My blade is sharp enough.

380
00:17:53,319 --> 00:17:55,039
I won't give them a chance to breathe.

381
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,880
All the documents are in here.

382
00:18:12,039 --> 00:18:13,160
And a new phone.

383
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:16,200
Cash and funds in overseas accounts,

384
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:17,559
all prepared in full for you.

385
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,000
Once the job is done,

386
00:18:19,759 --> 00:18:20,680
don't come back.

387
00:18:20,799 --> 00:18:21,880
Send word by phone that you're safe,

388
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,359
then leave the country immediately.

389
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:26,519
Once I wrap things up here,

390
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,240
I'll naturally arrange for you and your sister

391
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,200
to be reunited.

392
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:35,880
Thank you, Boss.
